  "prompt": "How does the legal system address complex money laundering schemes?",
  "response": "The legal system addresses complex money laundering schemes through several key strategies, including:\n\n1. Anti-Money Laundering (AML) Laws\n- Comprehensive legislative frameworks\n- Reporting requirements for financial institutions\n- Mandatory suspicious transaction reporting\n\n2. International Cooperation\n- Information sharing between countries\n- Extradition agreements\n- Mutual legal assistance treaties\n\n3. Investigative Techniques\n- Financial forensic analysis\n- Electronic transaction tracing\n- Undercover operations\n- Advanced data analytics\n\n4. Prosecution Approaches\n- Complex financial crime units\n- Specialized prosecutors\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture laws\n\n5. Regulatory Oversight\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Bank monitoring requirements\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n\nThese methods help detect, investigate, and prosecute sophisticated money laundering activities across different jurisdictions.\n\nNote: This overview reflects general legal approaches without referencing specific ongoing investigations or sensitive details.",
